<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,908,1583]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1448,1475]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Comments</emphasis>
: “P.N.G.” on the label appears to refer to Garamba National park, which borders 
<collectingCountry box="[1251,1398,1449,1475]" name="South Sudan" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">South Sudan</collectingCountry>
. H. De Saeger was an entomologist and secretary of national parks in the 
<collectingCountry box="[955,1032,1485,1511]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Congo</collectingCountry>
, who led many collecting trips and long-term ecological studies in that park. The “II/fd/17” on the label apparently is a code referring to a park location.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
